## Tone knobs (choose deliberately per post)

Dial these up/down before you write the first sentence.

- **Immediacy** (how fast readers get value)
  - Low: reflective essays, ethos pieces
  - High: tutorials, “how I built X”, recipes
- **Rigor** (how explicit your reasoning + tradeoffs are)
  - Low: gallery posts, lightweight notes
  - High: system design, networking, economy, AI behaviors
- **Poetry** (metaphor, cadence, fragments)
  - Low: technical docs, reference pages
  - High: “Why I Build” style, manifesto notes
- **Warmth** (direct address, empathy, openness)
  - Low: sterile/academic (avoid)
  - High: “I’m worried. I’m excited.” / “This sounds simple. It is not.”

Rule: **Don’t max all knobs at once.** Pick one primary and one secondary.

