## Anti-patterns (what to cut on sight)

- **Hype verbs**: “crushed”, “insane”, “game-changing”, “revolutionary”
- **Vague claims**: “it’s important”, “it’s interesting”, “it’s powerful”
- **Authority cosplay**: “as we all know”, “obviously”, “clearly”
- **Unpriced opinions**: strong takes without constraints, examples, or tradeoffs
- **Over-fragmentation**: too many poetic fragments without a thesis

### AI tells (cut these too)

**Hedging/throat-clearing:**

- "It's important to note...", "It is worth mentioning..."
- "But it wasn't just X—Y" (over-explains the pivot)

**Grandiose verbs:**

- Delve, Dive into, Embrace, Empower, Foster, Navigate, Unveil, Enhance

**Vague grandeur nouns:**

- Landscape, Realm, Tapestry, Journey (unless literal)

**Overwrought adjectives:**

- Vibrant, Intricate, Meticulous, Cutting-edge, Rapidly evolving

**Cliché openers/phrases:**

- "In this day and age", "At the end of the day", "In the realm of"
- "Picture this", "A testament to...", "Fast-paced world"

**Overused transitions:**

- Furthermore, Moreover, Additionally, Consequently, As a result
- "In other words", "In conclusion"

**Structural tells:**

- Repetitive sentence structures (same rhythm, same length)
- Excessive qualification before every claim
- Over-structured (too many numbered lists, too-clean headers)

